{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_2889c783affeUIX3gr9Z6cf87u","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d77639a09001wdkQGfN9f5gZUc","parts":[{"id":"prt_d7763a24e0011HdSvXmBMHcIgt","messageID":"msg_d77639a09001wdkQGfN9f5gZUc","sessionID":"ses_2889c783affeUIX3gr9Z6cf87u","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1edd291c040f450e9cdee713","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md"},"output":"<path>/workspace/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: [![GitHub license](https://img.shields.io/github/license/materialsvirtuallab/monty)](https://github.com/materialsvirtuallab/monty/blob/main/LICENSE)\n2: [![Linting](https://github.com/materialsvirtuallab/monty/workflows/Linting/badge.svg)](https://github.com/materialsvirtuallab/monty/workflows/Linting/badge.svg)\n3: [![Testing](https://github.com/materialsvirtuallab/monty/workflows/Testing/badge.svg)](https://github.com/materialsvirtuallab/monty/workflows/Testing/badge.svg)\n4: [![Downloads](https://static.pepy.tech/badge/monty)](https://pepy.tech/project/monty)\n5: [![codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/materialsvirtuallab/monty/branch/master/graph/badge.svg?token=QdfT2itxgu)](https://codecov.io/gh/materialsvirtuallab/monty)\n6: \n7: # Monty: Python Made Even Easier\n8: \n9: Monty is the missing complement to Python. Monty implements supplementary\n10: useful functions for Python that are not part of the standard library.\n11: Examples include useful utilities like transparent support for zipped files,\n12: useful design patterns such as singleton and cached_class, and many more.\n13: \n14: Python is a great programming language and comes with \"batteries\n15: included\". However, even Python has missing functionality and/or quirks that\n16: make it more difficult to do many simple tasks. In the process of\n17: creating several large scientific frameworks based on Python,\n18: my co-developers and I have found that it is often useful to create\n19: reusable utility  functions to supplement the Python standard library. Our\n20: forays in various developer sites and forums also found that many developers\n21: are looking for solutions to the same problems.\n22: \n23: Monty is created to serve as a complement to the Python standard library. It\n24: provides suite of tools to solve many common problems, and hopefully,\n25: be a resource to collect the best solutions.\n26: \n27: Monty supports Python 3.9+.\n28: \n29: Please visit the [official docs](https://materialsvirtuallab.github.io/monty) for more information.\n\n(End of file - total 29 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"[![GitHub license](https://img.shields.io/github/license/materialsvirtuallab/monty)](https://github.com/materialsvirtuallab/monty/blob/main/LICENSE)\n[![Linting](https://github.com/materialsvirtuallab/monty/workflows/Linting/badge.svg)](https://github.com/materialsvirtuallab/monty/workflows/Linting/badge.svg)\n[![Testing](https://github.com/materialsvirtuallab/monty/workflows/Testing/badge.svg)](https://github.com/materialsvirtuallab/monty/workflows/Testing/badge.svg)\n[![Downloads](https://static.pepy.tech/badge/monty)](https://pepy.tech/project/monty)\n[![codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/materialsvirtuallab/monty/branch/master/graph/badge.svg?token=QdfT2itxgu)](https://codecov.io/gh/materialsvirtuallab/monty)\n\n# Monty: Python Made Even Easier\n\nMonty is the missing complement to Python. Monty implements supplementary\nuseful functions for Python that are not part of the standard library.\nExamples include useful utilities like transparent support for zipped files,\nuseful design patterns such as singleton and cached_class, and many more.\n\nPython is a great programming language and comes with \"batteries\nincluded\". However, even Python has missing functionality and/or quirks that\nmake it more difficult to do many simple tasks. In the process of\ncreating several large scientific frameworks based on Python,\nmy co-developers and I have found that it is often useful to create\nreusable utility  functions to supplement the Python standard library. Our\nforays in various developer sites and forums also found that many developers","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"README.md","time":{"start":1775824511855,"end":1775824511866}}}]}
